From: Martin Pluskal <mpluskal@suse.com>
Subject: [PATCH] proto: route protobuf >= 6 to the v6 gencode

The bundled v6 protobuf stubs are forward-compatible with newer protobuf
runtimes per protobuf's cross-version runtime guarantee
(https://protobuf.dev/support/cross-version-runtime-guarantee):
ValidateProtobufRuntimeVersion only rejects a runtime OLDER than the linked
gencode, never a newer one. openSUSE Tumbleweed and Arch already ship
protobuf 7.x (Python runtime major 7), on which the previous strict
`major == 6` check raised "Unsupported protobuf version: 7.x". Routing
major >= 6 to the v6 stubs restores import on protobuf 7+ while staying
correct for protobuf 6.
---
--- a/src/xai_sdk/proto/__init__.py
+++ b/src/xai_sdk/proto/__init__.py
@@ -34,7 +34,7 @@
         video_pb2,
         video_pb2_grpc,
     )
-elif version.parse(google.protobuf.__version__).major == 6:
+elif version.parse(google.protobuf.__version__).major >= 6:
     from .v6 import (
         auth_pb2,
         auth_pb2_grpc,
